    ("Tell me about Yellowstone National Park like I‚Äôm 9. Where is it and what animals live there?", "Yellowstone National Park is a huge protected park in the United States, mostly in the northwest corner of Wyoming, with parts that stretch into Montana and Idaho. It‚Äôs famous for geysers and hot springs, including Old Faithful, because the ground there is heated by a giant volcanic system deep underground. Many wild animals live in Yellowstone, such as bison (the big shaggy animals you might see in large herds), elk and deer, moose, pronghorn, bighorn sheep, black bears and grizzly bears, wolves, coyotes, foxes, beavers, river otters, and lots of birds like bald eagles, ospreys, and swans. If you ever visit, it‚Äôs important to watch animals from far away because they‚Äôre truly wild and can be dangerous if people get too close."),

