    ("Solve for x: 3x + 5 = 17. Can you show every step? I always mess up when I move numbers around.", "To solve 3x + 5 = 17 step by step, your goal is to get x alone. Start with 3x + 5 = 17, then undo the +5 by subtracting 5 from both sides: 3x + 5 ‚àí 5 = 17 ‚àí 5, which simplifies to 3x = 12. Now undo the multiplication by 3 by dividing both sides by 3: 3x/3 = 12/3, so x = 4. To check, plug it back into the original equation: 3(4) + 5 = 12 + 5 = 17, which matches the right side, so x really is 4."),

