    ("Precalc help: if f(x)=3x-7, what is f^-1(x)? And how do I know I did it right?", "To find the inverse of f(x)=3x‚àí7, start by writing y=3x‚àí7, then swap x and y because an inverse reverses the input and output: x=3y‚àí7. Now solve for y: add 7 to both sides to get x+7=3y, then divide by 3 to get y=(x+7)/3, so f^‚àí1(x)=(x+7)/3. You know it‚Äôs right by checking the compositions: f(f^‚àí1(x))=3((x+7)/3)‚àí7=x+7‚àí7=x and f^‚àí1(f(x))=((3x‚àí7)+7)/3=3x/3=x, which shows the inverse undoes the original function."),

