    ("Operations research / optimization: I have 3 homework assignments and only 5 hours. Each one is worth points‚Äîhow do I set up a model to maximize my grade?", "Model it as a ‚Äúknapsack‚Äù (or time-allocation) optimization problem. Define decision variables xi for i = 1,2,3 where xi = 1 if you complete homework i (or xi is the fraction you complete if partial credit is allowed). Let ti be the hours required for homework i and pi be the points it‚Äôs worth (or expected points you can earn if you do it). Your goal is maximize total points: maximize p1x1 + p2x2 + p3x3, subject to the time limit t1x1 + t2x2 + t3x3 ‚â§ 5, and constraints 0 ‚â§ xi ‚â§ 1; if it‚Äôs all-or-nothing grading then add xi ‚àà {0,1}. If partial work earns proportional credit, keep xi continuous between 0 and 1; if partial credit is not proportional, you can approximate it by splitting each assignment into chunks (for example, problems or sections) with their own time and point values and use the same setup with more variables. Once you plug in your actual times and points, you can solve by checking all 2^3 = 8 combinations in the all-or-nothing case, or by choosing the highest ‚Äúpoints per hour‚Äù first in the proportional partial-credit case (while respecting any minimum time needed to get any credit, which would require the binary version)."),

