    ("I have a gas laws problem: a 2.0 L sample of gas at 1.2 atm is compressed to 0.80 L at constant temp. What‚Äôs the new pressure and can you show the setup?", "Because the temperature is constant, use Boyle‚Äôs law, which says P1V1 = P2V2. Set it up with the given values: (1.2 atm)(2.0 L) = P2(0.80 L). Solve for the new pressure by dividing both sides by 0.80 L: P2 = (1.2 atm √ó 2.0 L) / 0.80 L = 2.4 / 0.80 = 3.0 atm, so the pressure increases to 3.0 atm when the volume is compressed to 0.80 L."),

