    ("Solve for x: 3x + 5 = 26. Also can you show me the steps so I can do similar ones?", "To solve 3x + 5 = 26, isolate x by undoing operations in reverse order: first subtract 5 from both sides to undo the +5, giving 3x + 5 ‚àí 5 = 26 ‚àí 5, so 3x = 21. Next divide both sides by 3 to undo the multiplication by 3, giving 3x/3 = 21/3, so x = 7. You can check by plugging it back in: 3(7) + 5 = 21 + 5 = 26, which matches the original equation, so x = 7 is correct; for similar problems, always ‚Äúundo‚Äù addition/subtraction first, then undo multiplication/division, doing the same thing to both sides each time."),

