    ("What does the American flag colors mean? And why are there 50 stars?", "The American flag‚Äôs colors have traditional meanings that come from the Great Seal of the United States: red stands for valor and bravery, white stands for purity and innocence, and blue stands for vigilance, perseverance, and justice. There are 50 stars because each star represents one U.S. state, so the flag has one star for every state in the country today; the stars were updated as new states joined, and the current 50-star flag began in 1960 after Hawaii became the 50th state. The 13 stripes (7 red and 6 white) also have meaning because they remember the original 13 colonies that became the first states."),

