    ("We‚Äôre learning about community helpers in 2nd grade‚Äîwhat are some examples of community helpers and what does each one do?", "Community helpers are people who work to keep a community safe, healthy, and running smoothly. For example, a firefighter puts out fires and helps in emergencies, a police officer helps keep people safe and follows up when rules are broken, a doctor and a nurse help you stay healthy by checking your body and treating sickness or injuries, a dentist takes care of your teeth by cleaning them and fixing cavities, a teacher helps children learn skills like reading and math, a librarian helps people find books and learn how to use the library, a mail carrier delivers letters and packages to homes and businesses, a sanitation worker picks up trash and recycling to keep the town clean, a bus driver safely drives people to school or work, and a crossing guard helps children cross the street safely near schools. All of these jobs help everyone in the community, and you can often spot them by what they do and the tools they use, like a fire truck, a stethoscope, books, mail, or a stop sign."),

