    ("Was the Industrial Revolution mostly good or mostly bad for workers? I need 2 pros and 2 cons for my notes.", "For workers, the Industrial Revolution was a mix of benefits and harms, so whether it was ‚Äúmostly‚Äù good or bad depends on the time and place, but it often brought serious short-term suffering alongside some long-term gains. Two pros were that factories and mines created many new paid jobs (especially for people leaving farms), and over time industrial growth helped raise average wages and living standards for many workers, especially as skills, productivity, and later reforms increased pay and made goods like clothing and tools cheaper. Two cons were that early factory work was often dangerous and unhealthy, with long hours, low pay, frequent injuries, and polluted air, and that workers had little protection or power at first, including widespread child labor and harsh discipline, with few safety rules, no job security, and limited rights to organize until later labor laws and unions improved conditions."),

