    ("For civics, what are taxes for and what‚Äôs the difference between sales tax and income tax? Keep it simple please.", "Taxes are money people and businesses pay to the government so it can fund public services everyone uses, like schools, roads and bridges, police and fire departments, courts, parks, public health programs, and national defense, and they can also help pay for programs like Social Security and Medicare. Sales tax is a tax added to the price when you buy certain goods or services, so you pay it at the store at the time of purchase (for example, a $10 item might cost $10 plus sales tax), while income tax is a tax on the money you earn from a job or other income, usually taken out of each paycheck or paid when you file your taxes. In simple terms, sales tax is based on what you spend, and income tax is based on what you earn."),

