    ("What‚Äôs the difference between climate vs weather? My teacher keeps saying ‚Äòweather is day to day‚Äô but I still don‚Äôt get it.", "Weather is what the atmosphere is doing right now or over the next few days in a specific place, like ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs raining this afternoon,‚Äù ‚ÄúIt will be windy tomorrow,‚Äù or ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs 30¬∞C today,‚Äù and it can change quickly from hour to hour. Climate is the usual pattern of weather for a region over a long time, typically described using averages and ranges over about 30 years, like ‚ÄúThis area has hot, dry summers and mild, wetter winters,‚Äù or ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs usually snowy in January here,‚Äù and it changes much more slowly. A helpful way to remember it is: weather is your outfit today, climate is your whole wardrobe‚Äîone day can be unusually hot or cold, but climate tells you what kinds of days are common most years."),

