    ("How do you tell time with the little hand and big hand? Like if the big hand is on the 8, what does that mean?", "On an analog clock, the big hand is the minute hand and the little hand is the hour hand: the big hand tells how many minutes past the hour, and each number it points to counts as 5 minutes (1 means 5 minutes, 2 means 10, 3 means 15, and so on). So if the big hand is on the 8, that means 8 groups of 5 minutes have passed, which is 8 x 5 = 40 minutes, so you say ‚Äú:40‚Äù or ‚Äúforty minutes past.‚Äù Then you look at the little hand to see the hour: if the little hand is on 3 (or between 3 and 4), the time would be 3:40; if it‚Äôs on 7 (or between 7 and 8), it would be 7:40, and notice that when it‚Äôs :40 the little hand is usually more than halfway to the next number because the hour is getting close to changing."),

