    ("In linear algebra we‚Äôre doing systems of equations and row reduction‚Äîcan you check if I did this right? Solve: 2x y + z = 1, x + 3y 2z = 4, 3x + 2y + z = 7.", "Start by eliminating x using the first equation: from 2x ‚àí y + z = 1 you get x = (1 + y ‚àí z)/2. Substitute this into x + 3y ‚àí 2z = 4 to get (1 + y ‚àí z)/2 + 3y ‚àí 2z = 4, which simplifies to 7y ‚àí 5z = 7, and substitute into 3x + 2y + z = 7 to get 3(1 + y ‚àí z)/2 + 2y + z = 7, which simplifies to 7y ‚àí z = 11. Now solve the two-equation system 7y ‚àí 5z = 7 and 7y ‚àí z = 11 by subtracting the first from the second: (7y ‚àí z) ‚àí (7y ‚àí 5z) = 11 ‚àí 7 gives 4z = 4 so z = 1, then plug into 7y ‚àí z = 11 to get 7y ‚àí 1 = 11 so y = 12/7. Finally plug y and z into x = (1 + y ‚àí z)/2: x = (1 + 12/7 ‚àí 1)/2 = (12/7)/2 = 6/7. Quick check: 2(6/7) ‚àí 12/7 + 1 = 12/7 ‚àí 12/7 + 1 = 1, (6/7) + 3(12/7) ‚àí 2(1) = 6/7 + 36/7 ‚àí 14/7 = 28/7 = 4, and 3(6/7) + 2(12/7) + 1 = 18/7 + 24/7 + 7/7 = 49/7 = 7, so the solution is x = 6/7, y = 12/7, z = 1."),

