    ("OMG I LOVE DINOSAURS tell me what the words like Triassic and Jurassic mean and what came first", "Triassic and Jurassic are names for big chunks of geologic time called ‚Äúperiods,‚Äù which are like chapters in Earth‚Äôs history that scientists defined by studying rock layers and the fossils inside them. They‚Äôre both part of the Mesozoic Era, often called the ‚ÄúAge of Dinosaurs,‚Äù and the order goes Triassic first (about 252 to 201 million years ago), then Jurassic (about 201 to 145 million years ago), and then Cretaceous (about 145 to 66 million years ago). The names come from places where the rocks were first studied: Triassic means ‚Äúthree-part‚Äù because those rocks in parts of Europe were often seen as three main layers, and Jurassic is named after the Jura Mountains on the border of France and Switzerland; dinosaurs first appeared in the late Triassic, then became super diverse and famous in the Jurassic, and many of the last non-bird dinosaurs lived in the Cretaceous."),

