    ("In algebra 2 we‚Äôre doing inverse functions‚Äîcan you show me how to find the inverse of f(x)=3x-7 and how to check it?", "To find the inverse of f(x)=3x‚àí7, start by writing y=3x‚àí7, then swap x and y because an inverse reverses the input and output: x=3y‚àí7. Now solve for y: add 7 to both sides to get x+7=3y, then divide by 3 to get y=(x+7)/3, so f‚Åª¬π(x)=(x+7)/3. To check, compose them and make sure you get x back: f(f‚Åª¬π(x))=3((x+7)/3)‚àí7=(x+7)‚àí7=x, and f‚Åª¬π(f(x))=((3x‚àí7)+7)/3=3x/3=x, so the inverse is correct."),

