    ("I‚Äôm learning SQL‚Äîhow do I write a query that returns students with a grade above 90 AND sorts highest to lowest?", "To return only students with a grade above 90 and sort them from highest to lowest, you use a WHERE clause to filter and an ORDER BY clause with DESC to sort, for example: SELECT student_id, student_name, grade FROM students WHERE grade > 90 ORDER BY grade DESC; this will list all rows where grade is greater than 90, with the highest grades first (and if you want a consistent order when two students have the same grade, you can add a tie-breaker like ORDER BY grade DESC, student_name ASC)."),

