    ("is 25% the same as 1/4? my teacher said it is but i don\'t get why", "Yes, 25% is exactly the same as 1/4, just written in different forms. ‚ÄúPercent‚Äù means ‚Äúout of 100,‚Äù so 25% means 25 out of 100, which is the fraction 25/100; if you simplify 25/100 by dividing the top and bottom by 25, you get 1/4. You can also see it as a decimal: 1/4 means 1 divided by 4, and that division is exact because 4 goes into 1 as 0.25 (since 0.25 √ó 4 = 1), and 0.25 is the same as 25/100, which is 25%."),

    # Auto-added 2025-12-26 02:17 - Category: simple_machines_intro
    ("what are simple machines? can you tell me what a lever and a pulley do with kid examples", "Simple machines are basic tools that make work easier by changing how a force is used, such as making you need less effort, letting you push or pull in a more helpful direction, or spreading the work out over a longer distance; common simple machines include the lever and the pulley. A lever is a stiff bar that pivots on a point called a fulcrum, and it helps you lift or move something heavy by pushing down on one end to raise the other end, like using a seesaw at the playground, using a crowbar to pry up a stuck rock, or using the handle of a bottle opener to lift a cap. A pulley is a wheel with a groove that a rope runs through, and it helps you lift things by changing the direction you pull (so you can pull down to lift something up) and, when you use more than one pulley together, it can also reduce how hard you have to pull; kid examples include the rope-and-wheel at a flagpole that lets you pull down to raise a flag, the pulley on a window-blind cord, or a small pulley system used to lift a heavy bucket in a well or to hoist a bike in a garage."),

