    ("can you help me write basic HTML for a simple page with a title, a picture, and a list? i keep forgetting the tags", "Here‚Äôs a simple ‚Äústarter‚Äù HTML page that includes the main tags you‚Äôre likely forgetting: the document type, html, head, title, body, a heading, an image, and a list. You can copy this and then just change the text and the image filename: <!doctype html> <html lang=\"en\"> <head> <meta charset=\"utf-8\"> <title>My Simple Page</title> </head> <body> <h1>My Simple Page</h1> <img src=\"picture.jpg\" alt=\"A description of the picture\" width=\"300\"> <h2>My List</h2> <ul> <li>First item</li> <li>Second item</li> <li>Third item</li> </ul> </body> </html> The key tags to remember are: title goes inside head (it‚Äôs what shows on the browser tab), h1 is a big page heading, img shows a picture using src for the file/URL and alt for a text description, and ul makes a bulleted list with each item in an li (if you want a numbered list instead, swap ul for ol)."),

