    ("I‚Äôm doing a poster: who were 2 important American inventors and what did they invent? (Not just Edison pls.)", "Two important American inventors you can feature are Alexander Graham Bell and the Wright brothers. Alexander Graham Bell (1847‚Äì1922) is best known for inventing the first practical telephone, which he patented in 1876 and which transformed long-distance communication by letting people talk instantly over wires. Orville Wright (1871‚Äì1948) and Wilbur Wright (1867‚Äì1912) invented the first successful powered airplane, the Wright Flyer, and made the first controlled, sustained flight on December 17, 1903, at Kitty Hawk, North Carolina, launching the modern age of aviation."),

