    ("I got this sequence/series question: does ‚àë(n=1 to ‚àû) (3^n)/(5^n) converge or diverge? And how do you know?", "The series ‚àë from n=1 to ‚àû of (3^n)/(5^n) is the same as ‚àë from n=1 to ‚àû of (3/5)^n, which is a geometric series with common ratio r = 3/5. A geometric series converges exactly when the absolute value of the ratio is less than 1, and here |3/5| = 0.6 < 1, so the series converges. In fact, since it starts at n=1, its sum is r/(1 ‚àí r) = (3/5)/(1 ‚àí 3/5) = (3/5)/(2/5) = 3/2, which also confirms it converges to a finite value rather than diverging."),

