    ("Discrete math/combinatorics help: how many 8-character passwords have at least 1 digit and at least 1 uppercase letter (repetition allowed)? Please do it with inclusion‚Äìexclusion so I can learn it.", "Assume each of the 8 characters can be any uppercase letter A‚ÄìZ or any digit 0‚Äì9 (so 36 choices per position) and repetition is allowed. Let the total set be all length-8 strings from these 36 symbols, so there are 36^8 total. Use inclusion‚Äìexclusion on the ‚Äúbad‚Äù sets: let A be the set with no digits (all characters are letters), and let B be the set with no uppercase letters (all characters are digits). Then |A| = 26^8 because each position must be one of 26 letters, and |B| = 10^8 because each position must be one of 10 digits. The overlap A ‚à© B would mean ‚Äúno digits and no letters‚Äù at the same time, which is impossible here, so |A ‚à© B| = 0. Therefore the number with at least one digit and at least one uppercase letter is 36^8 ‚àí |A ‚à™ B| = 36^8 ‚àí (|A| + |B| ‚àí |A ‚à© B|) = 36^8 ‚àí 26^8 ‚àí 10^8."),

