    ("If I roll a die 20 times, how do I keep track and figure out which number I got the most?", "To keep track of 20 die rolls and figure out which number you got the most, make a simple tally chart for the numbers 1 through 6: write ‚Äú1 2 3 4 5 6‚Äù on paper, then each time you roll, add one tally mark next to the number you rolled (for example, if you roll a 4, add a mark next to 4). After all 20 rolls, count the tally marks for each number; those counts are the frequencies, and the number with the largest count is the one you got most often (the ‚Äúmode‚Äù). For example, if your counts end up as 1:3, 2:2, 3:5, 4:4, 5:4, 6:2, then 3 is the most common because it appeared 5 times; if two numbers tie for the largest count, then you got a tie for most common."),

