    ("I‚Äôm writing a lab report and I‚Äôm stuck: how do you find the mean, median, and range from this data set: 8, 10, 10, 12, 15, 15, 19?", "First, make sure the data are in order (they already are): 8, 10, 10, 12, 15, 15, 19. The mean is the average, so add them up and divide by how many numbers there are: 8 + 10 + 10 + 12 + 15 + 15 + 19 = 89, and there are 7 values, so mean = 89/7 ‚âà 12.71. The median is the middle value when the data are ordered; with 7 values, the 4th value is the middle, so the median is 12. The range measures spread and equals the largest minus the smallest value, so range = 19 ‚àí 8 = 11."),

