    ("My code won‚Äôt run and I‚Äôm frustrated. I‚Äôm using Scratch and my sprite isn‚Äôt moving even though I have a \'when green flag clicked\' block. What are some debugging tricks?", "In Scratch, a ‚Äúwhen green flag clicked‚Äù block only starts a script, so the best debugging trick is to prove each piece works one step at a time: first click the script itself (not the flag) to see if it runs, and add a quick ‚Äúsay [started] for 2 seconds‚Äù right under the green-flag block so you know the script is actually triggering; if the sprite still doesn‚Äôt move, check that the movement blocks are attached to that same script and not floating loose, and that you‚Äôre using ‚Äúmove (10) steps‚Äù or ‚Äúchange x by (10)‚Äù (not ‚Äúset x to (10)‚Äù which might look like it‚Äôs stuck if it keeps setting the same value). Make sure nothing else is fighting your movement, like another script that constantly sets x/y back to a fixed position, a ‚Äúgo to x: y:‚Äù inside a forever loop, or a ‚Äústop [all]‚Äù block running early; you can temporarily disable other scripts by dragging them away from their event blocks or adding a ‚Äúwait (1) seconds‚Äù at the top to see which script is taking control. Also check simple gotchas: the sprite might be hidden (use ‚Äúshow‚Äù), might be moving but instantly bouncing back because of ‚Äúif on edge, bounce‚Äù plus rotation style issues (try setting rotation style to ‚Äúleft-right‚Äù or ‚Äúdon‚Äôt rotate‚Äù), might be moving off-screen (add ‚Äúgo to x:0 y:0‚Äù at start), or you might be clicking the Stage while your code is on a different sprite (make sure the correct sprite is selected and the blocks are on it). Finally, use the built-in watchers as a debugger: right-click a variable and ‚Äúshow‚Äù it, or create a variable like ‚Äúdebug‚Äù and set it to different numbers at key points (‚Äúset debug to 1‚Äù, then 2, then 3) so you can see how far the script gets, and if you‚Äôre using clones, remember clones need ‚Äúwhen I start as a clone‚Äù and the original sprite won‚Äôt move if only the clone script has the movement."),

