    ("I got a dataset of quiz scores: 70, 85, 85, 90, 95, 60, 70. Can you find the mean, median, mode, and range and explain what each means?", "For the quiz scores 70, 85, 85, 90, 95, 60, 70, first sort them: 60, 70, 70, 85, 85, 90, 95. The mean (average) is the total divided by how many scores there are: 60 + 70 + 70 + 85 + 85 + 90 + 95 = 555, and 555 √∑ 7 ‚âà 79.29, so the mean is about 79.3 points; this tells you the overall average score. The median is the middle value when the data are sorted; since there are 7 scores, the 4th score is the middle, so the median is 85, meaning half the scores are at or below 85 and half are at or above 85. The mode is the most frequent score; here 70 appears twice and 85 appears twice (all others appear once), so the data are bimodal with modes 70 and 85, which tells you the most common scores. The range is the highest minus the lowest score: 95 ‚àí 60 = 35, which tells you how spread out the scores are from the smallest to the largest."),

