    ("can you show me how to balance this equation step by step: Al + O2 -> Al2O3", "Start with the unbalanced equation Al + O2 -> Al2O3 and balance one element at a time: oxygen is tricky because it appears as O2 on the left but as O3 in Al2O3 on the right, so make the number of oxygen atoms match by using the least common multiple of 2 and 3, which is 6; put a 3 in front of O2 to make 6 oxygen atoms on the left (3O2), and put a 2 in front of Al2O3 to make 6 oxygen atoms on the right (2Al2O3). Now count aluminum: the right side has 2 √ó 2 = 4 aluminum atoms, so put a 4 in front of Al on the left to match. The balanced equation is 4Al + 3O2 -> 2Al2O3, and you can quickly check it: left has 4 Al and 3√ó2 = 6 O, right has 2√ó2 = 4 Al and 2√ó3 = 6 O, so both sides match."),

