    ("what does ‚Äúmean, median, mode, range‚Äù actually tell you? can you use this set: 4, 7, 7, 9, 12, 13", "Using the data set 4, 7, 7, 9, 12, 13, these four measures each tell a different ‚Äúquick story‚Äù about the numbers. The mean is the average, which gives a single typical value if you spread the total evenly: the sum is 4 + 7 + 7 + 9 + 12 + 13 = 52, and 52 √∑ 6 = 8.666‚Ä¶ (about 8.67), so the mean says the data balance point is a little under 9. The median is the middle value when the numbers are in order (they already are); with 6 numbers you take the two middle ones, 7 and 9, and average them, so the median is (7 + 9) √∑ 2 = 8, which tells you the ‚Äúmiddle‚Äù of the set and is less affected by an unusually low or high value like 4 or 13. The mode is the most frequent value; 7 appears twice while the others appear once, so the mode is 7, telling you the most common score in the list. The range is the spread from smallest to largest, 13 ‚àí 4 = 9, telling you how wide the data are overall; here the values span 9 units from low to high."),

