    ("In digital logic, can you simplify this boolean expression using Karnaugh maps: F(A,B,C,D)=Œ£m(1,3,4,5,7,9,11,12,13,15)? I need the minimal SOP form.", "Put 1s in the 4-variable K-map for minterms 1,3,4,5,7,9,11,12,13,15 (with AB as rows in Gray order 00,01,11,10 and CD as columns in Gray order 00,01,11,10). You can form two 4-cell groups that cover eight of the 1s: the entire column CD=01 (minterms 1,5,13,9) gives C\'D, and the entire column CD=11 (minterms 3,7,15,11) gives CD. The remaining 1s are 4 and 12, which can be grouped together as a 2-cell pair at CD=00 across rows AB=01 and AB=11 (minterms 4 and 12), giving BC\'D\'. Combining these implicants yields the minimal SOP: F = C\'D + CD + BC\'D\'. (You can also notice C\'D + CD = D, so an equivalent minimal SOP is F = D + BC\'D\', and this matches exactly the given minterm set: all cases with D=1 are included, plus the extra D=0 cases where B=1 and C=0, namely minterms 4 and 12.)"),

