    ("I‚Äôm trying to understand machine learning basics‚Äîwhat‚Äôs the difference between training, validation, and test data in plain English?", "Training data is the examples you let the model learn from, meaning it repeatedly looks at these inputs (and usually the correct answers/labels) and adjusts its internal settings to get better on them, like a student practicing with an answer key. Validation data is a separate ‚Äúpractice exam‚Äù set that the model does not learn from directly, but you use it during development to make decisions such as which model version to keep, how complex it should be, when to stop training, or which settings (hyperparameters) work best; it helps you catch overfitting early without peeking at the final exam. Test data is the final, untouched ‚Äúreal exam‚Äù you save until the very end to get an honest estimate of how well the finished model will perform on new, unseen data in the real world, and it should not be used to tune choices because that would make the score overly optimistic."),

