    ("Can you balance this equation and explain the steps? Fe + O2 -> Fe2O3", "To balance Fe + O2 ‚Üí Fe2O3, first balance oxygen by finding a common number of O atoms: O2 has 2 oxygen atoms and Fe2O3 has 3, so the least common multiple is 6. Put 3 in front of O2 to make 3 √ó 2 = 6 O atoms on the left, and put 2 in front of Fe2O3 to make 2 √ó 3 = 6 O atoms on the right, giving Fe + 3O2 ‚Üí 2Fe2O3. Now balance iron: the right side has 2 √ó 2 = 4 Fe atoms, so put 4 in front of Fe on the left to get 4Fe + 3O2 ‚Üí 2Fe2O3. Final check confirms it‚Äôs balanced: left has Fe = 4 and O = 6, right has Fe = 4 and O = 6, so the balanced equation is 4Fe + 3O2 ‚Üí 2Fe2O3."),

