    ("can you help me do 7 x 8 in my head? like a trick so i dont count on my fingers", "Yes‚Äîhere are a couple of quick ‚Äúin-your-head‚Äù tricks for 7 √ó 8 that don‚Äôt use fingers. One easy method is to use 7 √ó 8 = 7 √ó (10 ‚àí 2): first do 7 √ó 10 = 70, then do 7 √ó 2 = 14, and subtract to get 70 ‚àí 14 = 56. Another fast method is to use doubles: 7 √ó 8 is ‚Äú7 times 8,‚Äù and 8 is 2 √ó 4, so do 7 √ó 4 = 28 (because 7 √ó 2 = 14 and doubling 14 gives 28), then double 28 to get 56; you can quickly check it makes sense because 7 √ó 7 = 49, so one more 7 gives 56."),

