    ("Solve for x please: 3x + 5 = 23. And explain it like I‚Äôm new to algebra.", "To solve 3x + 5 = 23, think of x as a mystery number and your job is to undo what‚Äôs being done to it, one step at a time. First undo the +5 by subtracting 5 from both sides so the equation stays balanced: 3x + 5 ‚àí 5 = 23 ‚àí 5, which simplifies to 3x = 18. Next undo the ‚Äú3 times x‚Äù by dividing both sides by 3: 3x √∑ 3 = 18 √∑ 3, so x = 6. You can check it by plugging 6 back in: 3(6) + 5 = 18 + 5 = 23, which matches, so x really is 6."),

