    ("What‚Äôs the easiest way to do 17√ó6 in your head? I have a timed quiz and I freak out.", "A fast, low-stress way to do 17√ó6 in your head is to break 17 into 10 and 7: 10√ó6 = 60 and 7√ó6 = 42, then add 60 + 42 = 102, so 17√ó6 = 102. If you like an even quicker ‚Äúadjust‚Äù trick, think 17√ó6 = (20√ó6) ‚àí (3√ó6) = 120 ‚àí 18 = 102; to stay calm on a timed quiz, take one breath and say the steps in your head as ‚Äútimes 10, times 7, add,‚Äù or ‚Äúminus 3,‚Äù because having a consistent mini-routine helps prevent freezing. You can quickly check your answer by estimating: 17 is close to 18, and 18√ó6 = 108, so 102 makes sense because it should be a little less than 108."),

