    ("what‚Äôs the carbon cycle in kid words? is it like pollution or different", "The carbon cycle is Earth‚Äôs ‚Äúcarbon recycling system,‚Äù where carbon (a tiny building-block atom in all living things) moves around again and again between the air, plants, animals, the ocean, and the ground. Plants pull carbon dioxide (CO2) out of the air to grow using sunlight, animals (and people) get that carbon by eating plants or other animals, and then breathing and rotting put CO2 back into the air; the ocean also soaks up some CO2 and can release it later, and over very long times some carbon gets stored in rocks and fossil fuels. Pollution is different: pollution means harmful stuff in the environment, but CO2 itself is a normal part of the carbon cycle; the problem is that burning coal, oil, and gas and cutting lots of forests adds extra CO2 faster than nature can take it back out, which makes the ‚Äúrecycling‚Äù unbalanced and can warm the planet."),

