    ("What is WPA3 and how does it improve security?",
     "WPA3 improvements over WPA2: 1) SAE (Simultaneous Authentication of Equals) - replaces PSK, resistant to offline dictionary attacks. 2) Forward secrecy - past sessions protected if key compromised. 3) 192-bit security mode for enterprise. 4) Protected Management Frames mandatory. 5) Easy Connect for IoT devices (QR code provisioning). 6) Enhanced Open for open networks (OWE - encrypted without password). Transition: use WPA3-Transition mode for compatibility with WPA2 devices. [Generation: Network security - WPA3 explained]"),
    ("How do I detect rogue access points?",
     "Rogue AP detection: 1) Wireless scanners: Kismet, Acrylic Wi-Fi, WiFi Analyzer. 2) WIDS/WIPS: AirMagnet, Cisco Wireless IPS. 3) Network side: monitor for unexpected DHCP servers, ARP anomalies. 4) MAC address analysis: compare to authorized AP list. 5) Signal triangulation in enterprise WLAN controllers. 6) Regular site surveys. 7) 802.1X - unauthorized APs can't authenticate. Signs: duplicate SSIDs, unusual signal locations, unknown MAC vendors. Policy: prohibit personal APs, educate users on evil twin attacks. [Generation: Network security - rogue AP detection]"),

